Three people were killed on Monday in a matatu accident in Nthia area, Makindu subcounty, Makueni county. Makueni county police commander Joseph Napeiyan said the 14-seater matatu rolled several times off the road after one of its tyres burst. The matatu was ferrying four passengers from Makindu to Wote town when the accident occurred. The matatu driver and conductor were among those killed in the accident. Maalim urged motorists to follow traffic rules. "We will be alert to ensure motorists follow traffic rules as we approach the festive season," he said.